.TH "ps3_event_receive_port_setup" 9 "ps3_event_receive_port_setup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ps3_event_receive_port_setup \- Setup an event receive port.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ps3_event_receive_port_setup
.BI "(enum ps3_cpu_binding cpu "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *virq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
enum ps3_cpu_binding indicating the cpu the interrupt should be
serviced on.
.IP "virq" 12
The assigned Linux virq.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The virq can be used with \fBlv1_connect_interrupt_event_receive_port\fP to
arrange to receive interrupts from system-bus devices, or with
\fBps3_send_event_locally\fP to signal events.
